snippet.textDisplay:
I feel a bit naive going into this by donating my time, connections and work to help procure products from China where I live and am now under quarantine in the USA which is my home country. The contents of this video is also one of the reasons why I decided only to work with vetted factories. But the world is also expending energy to find these factories so guess what, they're pretty booked up which means a delayed delivery and a huge MOQ (min order quantity).


After filtering out all the gougers and nonsense and bad FDA certs etc, I found solid factories to work with. Then comes the issue of getting buyers to commit to a production cycle. 5-7 day lead time, batch production, air shipment if you booked a slot on the plane's schedule. Did I mention the cost of air freight these days? To ship 100,000 masks costs $35,000. ouch.


The current state of factories making masks now is that they are all running 24/7. Factories charge 50/50 deposit/exwarehouse.
Masks costs anywhere from $1.80-$2.80 with 100,000 MOQs. So if you see N95 masks costing around $3/each landed in USA, don't be quick to judge that they are gouging.


There is the reseller market who have immediate inventory but these are traders so they add their markup to it. Problem with this is that you cannot know if there are any funny business with regards to FDA certification or CE. With the big buyers, they are used to paying FOB for merchandise already in the USA. It's a sellers market now and not a single factory I found can accept terms outside of ex-factory.

So, the way I see it is this. The Government must jump in and work with the CCP to secure/take over production lines but there's much ego at play so I do not see this happening. The French government worked a deal with the CCP and one of my vetted factories now got nabbed up yesterday for a huge production run such that all existing orders are now pushed to the back. From my observation, people who bought into the production line will now likely have to wait another 2 weeks. ouch.


My entreprenuer brain thinks that if we want to make a difference, must secure committed buyers who can pay for inspected goods at port stateside and raise capital from investors willing to take the risk to get products through the production cycle and landed in USA. This will likely then be a profit play unless investors have it in their hearts to 'loan' or gift the investment. Good luck everyone.

Some masks, if not made properly, actually can have loose particles from the fiber of the product, that could potentially be inhaled by the wearer 🤦.

I'm now wondering how many of these not certified or non quality inspected masks are floating around? 🤷

At least the ones in this video are from the States.

This type of person takes away from those who NEED them.

Things such as N-95 Masks, Latex-Free Gloves, Clorox/Lysol Wipes etc, Rubbing Alcohol and other things that we with low immune systems needed. The thing that is so Stupid is that stores still let people traipse through their store touching everything inside. They need to set up lines outside and have people come up to a tablet where they can order and pay for items in real time. After you pay someone else inside the store will gather and bag up your groceries and then they bring them up to a certain point where they are passed off to the first person that checked your ID. This means that someone can't just go and purchase certain items and then go to the next store and do the same thing HORDING things they don't need.

snippet.textDisplay: We need to just have several factories in the USA equipped to make all the PPE and the testing kits.  Its ridiculous to have so much made in an hostile communist nation.  We ought to declare it necessary for national defense and insure that we have a plentiful local source for these necessary items.  Our reliance on China is just disturbing.  The price gouging is insane. It doesn't look like its something super complicated to make.
